{
  "text": "Considering the results on Dirac operators on the non commutative sphere in [CITATION_1] , this should not come as a surprise that we cannot obey all the conditions. There the conclusion was to sacrifice the bimodule condition, which is (4) on our list, and replace it by the commutator being a compact operator. However we have kept all the algebraic conditions including the bimodule condition and ∇ S preserving j, kept D being hermitian and dropped only that J is an isometry in favour of some twisted q-version of that.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "15281954"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "15281954": {
      "title": "The spectral geometry of the equatorial Podles sphere",
      "abstract": "We propose a slight modification of the properties of a spectral geometry a la Connes, which allows for some of the algebraic relations to be satisfied only modulo compact operators. On the equatorial Podles sphere we construct suq2-equivariant Dirac operator and real structure which satisfy these modified properties."
    }
  }
}